+++++ Special Containment Procedures:
SCP-x004 cannot be contained, as its nature is to make itself unknowable, and thus is not a direct risk to the veil.

+++++ Description: 
SCP-x004 is an anti-memetic phenomenon that causes the brain of affected individuals to experience visual and auditory hallucinations, primarily overriding any information that doesn’t fit into their already understood worldview. This presents a unique threat to the foundation in that SCP-x004 itself cannot be observed and thus cannot breach the veil. In fact, SCP-x004's memetic properties seem to have an affect on the anomalous properties of any nearby SCPs, causing those nearby to be unable to perceive the anomaly properly. 

In this way, SCP-x004 is actually beneficial to the veil, as it prevents other more obvious anomalies from being observed by the public. However, at this point in time, there is no known method of effecting SCP-x004 in any way. 

SCP-x004 is an airborne substance that is completely indistinguishable from ordinary fog, and it is only visible when it collects in very large amounts. This dense clustering of fog can only be viewed from a distance, as approaching the cloud triggers the anti-memetic properties of SCP-x004.


